# Apache configuration for the pre-rendered single-page app.
#
# Each route is pre-rendered to its own <route>/index.html, but direct visits and
# deep links must always resolve to an app shell so React Router can take over on
# the client. Without this, Apache returns 403 Forbidden for any directory that
# has no index.html (e.g. /work/, or /work/<id>/ when that page was not uploaded)
# and 404 for client-only routes.
#
# This file is copied verbatim from public/ into the build/ root by Vite, so it
# lands at the deployed site root alongside index.html.
#
# IMPORTANT: the two absolute paths below must match the deployed base URL
# (VITE_APP_BASE_PATH). They are set for:
#   https://projects.cah.ucf.edu/mediaartsexhibits/elo2026/
# If the site is deployed under a different path, update both paths to match.

# Serve <dir>/index.html when it exists; otherwise fall back to the app shell
# instead of returning 403 for an empty or index-less directory.
DirectoryIndex index.html /mediaartsexhibits/elo2026/index.html

# For any request that does not map to a real file, serve the app shell (HTTP 200)
# so client-side routing can resolve the path.
FallbackResource /mediaartsexhibits/elo2026/index.html

# Do not expose raw directory listings.
# If this line causes an HTTP 500 error, the server's AllowOverride does not permit
# Options in .htaccess; remove this single line (the two directives above still work).
Options -Indexes
